## 5. Lexer Details

**[A] Technique used for pattern matching:**
DFA-based (deterministic finite automaton) pattern matching implemented as a single-pass `scan()` function using a switch-case on the current character with state managed via a `scanNext` flag for lookahead/retract.

**[B] Keyword Handling Technique:**
Keywords are stored in a hash map at initialization and looked up after scanning a FIELDID-pattern lexeme using `lookupKeyword()`.

**[C] Hash function description, if used for keyword handling:**
A polynomial rolling hash: `h = h * 31 + (unsigned char)s[i]`, result taken modulo `HASH_SIZE` (53). Collisions resolved via linear probing.

**[D] Have you used twin buffer?**
No

**[E] Error handling and reporting (yes/No):**
Yes

**[F] Describe the errors handled by you:**
Identifier/function name exceeding maximum length (20/30 characters), unrecognized characters, malformed operators (e.g. incomplete `!=`, `<--`, `&&&`, `@@@`), malformed real numbers (missing digits after decimal or after exponent `E`), and invalid identifier patterns.

**[G] Data Structure Description for tokenInfo (in maximum two lines):**
`Token` struct containing `TokenType type` (enum), `char lexeme[31]` (fixed-size string), `unsigned int lexemeSize`, and `unsigned int lineNo`. Tokens are stored in a dynamically resized `TokenList` (array of `Token` with `size` and `capacity`).

